        {
            "navLabel": "Kirkwood",
            "title": "Kirkwood — The First Suburb",
            "text": [
                "Kirkwood was platted in 1853 as the first planned suburban community west of the Mississippi River, designed deliberately away from the smoke and congestion of St. Louis — and specifically oriented around the railroad.",
                "Today its historic downtown retains much of that original DNA: a walkable grid, a functioning Amtrak station, and places like Picasso's Coffee House that have become neighborhood institutions."
            ],
            "callout": "Kirkwood's station is one of the few in the country where an active Amtrak stop sits in the middle of a walkable historic downtown.",
            "scene": {
