        {
            "navLabel": "The Full Picture",
            "title": "The County in Context",
            "text": [
                "Zooming back out, what strikes you about St. Louis County is the sheer density of distinct communities packed into a relatively compact geography. Over 90 incorporated municipalities occupy the county.",
                "That fragmentation is both a strength and a challenge — it produces hyper-local character and identity, but also fragments governance, services, and regional coordination.",
                "The coffee shops and bookstores scattered across this map are more than amenities. They are the gathering places where community identity gets built and maintained, one conversation at a time."
            ],
